WEBVTT

00:00.087 --> 00:02.681
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

00:05.564 --> 00:07.846
Everyone has
a date to the prom but me.

00:07.955 --> 00:09.502
I am the only one.

00:09.612 --> 00:11.502
Sue, I'm sure you're not
the only one.

00:11.579 --> 00:13.588
No, I am. It's true.

00:13.677 --> 00:16.651
You know, I heard that Beyoncé
never got asked to her prom.

00:17.387 --> 00:18.685
Really?

00:18.782 --> 00:21.073
<i>I had no idea if that was true.</i>

00:21.153 --> 00:22.632
<i>I mean,</i>
<i>it's certainly possible.</i>

00:22.780 --> 00:24.947
<i>You don't come out of the womb</i>
<i>lookin' like Beyoncé.</i>

00:25.064 --> 00:26.856
<i>She could've been awkward</i>
<i>in high school.</i>

00:27.085 --> 00:28.717
<i>What kind of name is "Beyoncé"?</i>

00:28.824 --> 00:30.904
<i>Is it French or did her parents</i>
<i>just make it up?</i>

00:31.032 --> 00:32.381
<i>Oh, I wish</i>
<i>I could speak French.</i>

00:32.465 --> 00:33.885
<i>God knows when I'd use it.</i>

00:33.962 --> 00:37.144
<i>But still, sometimes it's just</i>
<i>nice to be able to do stuff.</i>

00:37.971 --> 00:40.220
<i>Oh, my God. Your daughter is</i>
<i>pouring out her heart to you.</i>

00:40.349 --> 00:41.600
<i>Listen! Focus!</i>

00:41.668 --> 00:42.788
<i>Pay attention!</i>

00:42.872 --> 00:45.991
That is something
I've never told anyone ever.

00:46.569 --> 00:47.970
<i>Uh-oh.</i>
<i>She stopped talking.</i>

00:48.056 --> 00:48.891
<i>Say something.</i>

00:48.978 --> 00:50.158
<i>Take a shot.</i>

00:50.677 --> 00:53.467
Honey, I'm sure you will.

00:53.568 --> 00:56.558
Oh. Thanks, mom.

00:57.102 --> 00:58.273
<i>God, I'm good.</i>

00:59.573 --> 01:02.307
Axl, did you have Mrs. Danner
for sixth-grade English?

01:02.502 --> 01:04.759
Grandma arms, slight mustache?

01:04.924 --> 01:06.081
Yeah, I remember her.

01:06.207 --> 01:08.400
Well, she won't let us write
a normal book report --

01:08.511 --> 01:11.601
says we have to be creative
and "Think outside the book."

01:11.702 --> 01:12.425
I hate this.

01:12.521 --> 01:13.853
If they want us to think
outside the box,

01:13.943 --> 01:15.953
they should tell us
exactly how.

01:16.069 --> 01:18.657
Oh, yeah, I remember
that project.

01:18.741 --> 01:19.909
I did awesome on that.

01:19.973 --> 01:21.403
So you'll help me with mine?

01:21.513 --> 01:23.883
No, I was just telling you
how awesome I am.

01:23.986 --> 01:25.686
Hey, who helped you
drop all those classes

01:25.786 --> 01:27.469
so you wouldn't fail
out of school?

01:27.563 --> 01:28.862
And who allowed himself
to be farted on

01:28.943 --> 01:31.277
for the promise of a prize
that never came?

01:31.444 --> 01:33.922
As far as little brothers go,
you hit the jackpot.

01:34.057 --> 01:36.843
So, come on,
help a brother out.

01:39.216 --> 01:41.023
Sue, I need to talk to you
for a minute.

01:41.742 --> 01:43.648
Enjoy your potato.

01:46.329 --> 01:47.448
Oh, no.

01:47.551 --> 01:49.389
Am I over-chiving again?

01:49.519 --> 01:51.000
No, it's not about the chives.

01:51.085 --> 01:52.674
Although, you know
with the chives, less is more.

01:52.779 --> 01:54.201
This is non-work related.

01:54.377 --> 01:56.562
I'm gonna take off
my assistant-manager hat.

01:56.709 --> 01:57.638
I'm gonna talk to you

01:57.721 --> 01:59.691
as a fellow student
of Orson High --

01:59.851 --> 02:01.189
and a man.

02:01.943 --> 02:07.995
Anyway, I would like you
to accompany me to the prom.

02:09.020 --> 02:11.366
Really?

02:11.466 --> 02:12.741
Yes!
I'm going to prom!

02:12.835 --> 02:14.519
Whoo!

02:15.376 --> 02:16.212
Now back to work.

02:16.293 --> 02:17.748
Yes.

02:18.726 --> 02:21.163
<i>Dr. Oz says</i>
<i>sitting is the new smoking,</i>

02:21.274 --> 02:24.119
<i>so Mike and I decided to</i>
<i>haul our butts off the couch</i>

02:24.205 --> 02:25.475
<i>and take a walk.</i>

02:25.552 --> 02:27.530
<i>And while we may no longer</i>
<i>be dying from sitting,</i>

02:27.635 --> 02:31.214
<i>dying from boredom</i>
<i>was definitely a possibility.</i>

02:33.763 --> 02:36.633
<i>But then something amazing</i>
<i>happened -- well, someone.</i>

02:36.725 --> 02:37.518
<i>Well, someones.</i>

02:37.617 --> 02:39.311
<i>I'm saying</i>
<i>we ran into other people.</i>

02:39.449 --> 02:42.826
Hey! Vicki
from Mrs. Keats' class.

02:42.911 --> 02:44.596
Remember we sat next to each
other at back to school night?

02:44.714 --> 02:47.333
Yeah, thanks so much for
waking me up when I fell asleep.

02:47.409 --> 02:48.606
No problem.

02:48.698 --> 02:49.749
Hey, this is my husband, Mike.

02:49.824 --> 02:51.435
Hi. Nice to meet you.
This is my husband, Dale.

02:51.493 --> 02:52.157
Hey, I'm Dale.

02:56.046 --> 03:00.405
So, we get to my sister's house,
and we can't work <i> anything.</i>

03:00.505 --> 03:02.118
18 remotes --
we couldn't turn on the TV.

03:02.197 --> 03:04.310
It was like the whole house
was smarter than us.

03:04.411 --> 03:07.538
I swear, at one point, I think I
heard the oven laughing at me.

03:08.355 --> 03:09.463
- You work at Orson Quarry?
- Yeah.

03:09.546 --> 03:10.430
What's that like?

03:10.514 --> 03:12.862
Oh, well, have you seen "The Flintstones"?

03:12.968 --> 03:14.273
It's pretty much like that.

03:14.349 --> 03:15.291
Except at the end of the day,

03:15.361 --> 03:17.030
we <i> don't</i> slide down
the tail of a dinosaur.

03:17.096 --> 03:17.858
Oh, that's a bummer.

03:17.993 --> 03:19.070
Yeah.

03:19.139 --> 03:19.975
I hate to disappoint you.

03:21.176 --> 03:22.333
Well, this is our stop.

03:22.415 --> 03:23.277
- Oh.
- Oh.

03:23.379 --> 03:24.977
- This was great, guys.
- Yeah, do it again.

03:25.073 --> 03:26.489
- Okay, okay.
- Yeah.

03:26.584 --> 03:27.851
- Great.
- Take care.

03:27.949 --> 03:29.212
Bye!

03:29.727 --> 03:31.076
Well, that was pathetic.

03:31.159 --> 03:32.392
What do you mean?
I had fun.

03:32.467 --> 03:34.747
Yeah, of course you did, Mike.
You weren't talking to me.

03:34.821 --> 03:37.917
Hey, you were chattin' it up
pretty good with Dale yourself.

03:38.004 --> 03:39.656
It was like a one-woman show
back there.

03:39.754 --> 03:43.142
Tell me about it.
I was adorable -- witty, clever.

03:43.222 --> 03:45.030
I have never felt so alive.

03:45.130 --> 03:46.174
And <i> you?</i>

03:46.271 --> 03:47.960
You're totally bringing it
for Vicki.

03:48.100 --> 03:48.589
Eh.

03:48.681 --> 03:50.611
Yeah, you were talkative,
you were smiling.

03:50.696 --> 03:51.556
Don't you get it?

03:51.649 --> 03:54.345
That walk proves
that we can be fun and charming.

03:54.513 --> 03:56.388
But we shouldn't just bring it
for other people.

03:56.499 --> 03:58.243
We should bring it
for each other.

03:58.376 --> 03:59.072
Let's try it.

03:59.161 --> 04:00.824
Let's be interesting
for each other.

04:01.182 --> 04:01.833
Now?

04:01.925 --> 04:04.305
No, I'm tired now,
but we'll hit it hard tomorrow.

04:07.258 --> 04:08.847
I still don't get
what we're doing.

04:08.935 --> 04:10.578
Trust me.
It's gonna be awesome.

04:10.680 --> 04:12.077
You start with
the first book you ever read,

04:12.192 --> 04:14.614
then go all the way
to the last book you've read.

04:14.705 --> 04:16.904
It's your whole life's
journey in books.

04:16.998 --> 04:19.647
Then we knock them down like
dominos, video it,

04:19.762 --> 04:22.201
you show it in class --
"Boom!" -- they go nuts.

04:22.299 --> 04:23.236
Guaranteed A.

04:23.325 --> 04:24.013
But that doesn't have

04:24.115 --> 04:26.030
anything to do with
"The Old Man And The Sea."

04:26.103 --> 04:28.084
See? That's
your problem, Brick.

04:28.195 --> 04:29.784
You are a rigid thinker.

04:29.929 --> 04:31.761
That's why I'm gonna end up
ruling the world.

04:31.865 --> 04:34.999
All the big-time rich guys --
Steve Jobs...

04:36.273 --> 04:37.178
other guys --

04:37.295 --> 04:40.200
they're all creative thinkers,
risk-takers.

04:40.285 --> 04:42.105
I don't know about this, Axl.

04:42.185 --> 04:43.595
Wha-- look, that's fine.

04:43.695 --> 04:44.423
Go ahead.

04:44.507 --> 04:45.610
Dress like one of
the characters in the book

04:45.685 --> 04:47.838
and do a lame presentation
like a million other kids.

04:47.955 --> 04:50.032
What do <i> you</i> want, Brick?

04:50.142 --> 04:51.478
Do you want to go
the safe route,

04:51.598 --> 04:54.028
or do you want to be
an innovator,

04:54.133 --> 04:57.720
a trailblazer, a rule breaker?!

04:58.175 --> 04:59.180
I do.

04:59.263 --> 05:01.723
Then give me "One fish,
two fish, red fish, blue fish"

05:01.811 --> 05:03.210
and let's change the world!

05:03.802 --> 05:04.893
Yeah!

05:06.767 --> 05:08.425
Surprise!

05:08.506 --> 05:09.794
I'm here to take you to prom!

05:09.989 --> 05:10.929
What?

05:11.014 --> 05:12.363
Yeah, my mom
was talking to your mom,

05:12.465 --> 05:14.302
and she was saying how no one
had asked you to prom yet

05:14.399 --> 05:15.987
and how crazy that was.

05:16.123 --> 05:17.938
So my mom said, "It might
be nice if you'd take her,"

05:18.030 --> 05:19.775
and I said, "Are you kidding me?

05:19.916 --> 05:23.073
I'd do anything for Susie Q!"
You're like family.

05:23.169 --> 05:25.227
Oh! Wow, Sean.

05:25.316 --> 05:27.593
That is so incredibly nice!

05:27.741 --> 05:29.743
Actually,
the funny thing is --

05:29.819 --> 05:31.549
Yeah, my car broke down twice

05:31.645 --> 05:33.129
on the way down here
from Notre Dame,

05:33.207 --> 05:33.957
but I got it fixed.

05:34.045 --> 05:36.033
And I had to ask a professor
to move a big test,

05:36.138 --> 05:37.400
and I'm missing
my fraternity photo,

05:37.481 --> 05:39.442
but I said, "I don't care.

05:39.520 --> 05:42.711
I'm takin' Sue to her prom."
So, here I am.

05:44.013 --> 05:44.984
Well, great!

05:45.103 --> 05:46.294
- Yay!
- Yeah!

05:46.542 --> 05:47.807
Fun!

05:54.161 --> 05:57.279
<i>So, Sue had gone from no
dates to the prom to two dates --</i>

05:57.375 --> 06:00.077
<i>a problem she never in her life</i>
<i>could have anticipated.</i>

06:00.195 --> 06:01.961
<i>But since Sean had gone</i>
<i>to all that effort,</i>

06:02.050 --> 06:03.752
<i>Sue knew she had to do</i>
<i>the right thing</i>

06:03.869 --> 06:05.539
<i>and kick Edwin to the curb.</i>

06:05.652 --> 06:07.204
Okay, what color
are you wearing?

06:07.360 --> 06:11.243
Uh, green and burnt tangerine.

06:11.366 --> 06:12.562
No, silly, for the prom.

06:12.668 --> 06:13.995
'Cause I want to get
a matching cummerbund.

06:14.140 --> 06:14.712
Uh --

06:14.789 --> 06:16.118
Oh, and I'm gonna wear
my dress shoes,

06:16.217 --> 06:18.747
but can I put my jazz shoes
in your purse for dancing later?

06:18.918 --> 06:20.527
Brad, what are you
talking about?

06:20.606 --> 06:22.735
Prom. We always said that
if neither of us had a date,

06:22.820 --> 06:23.847
we'd be each other's date.

06:23.951 --> 06:26.205
I'm so glad I have you.
Otherwise, I'd be devastated.

06:26.327 --> 06:27.495
So, we're going together,
right?

06:29.583 --> 06:31.024
You bet!

06:33.312 --> 06:34.186
Hey, did I tell you we got

06:34.285 --> 06:36.980
those new rotary saliva ejectors
at work?

06:37.205 --> 06:38.174
Hm.

06:38.891 --> 06:41.088
Still gettin' spit on
a lot, though.

06:44.954 --> 06:46.696
Got to get working
on those taxes.

06:46.986 --> 06:48.054
Yep.

06:48.215 --> 06:50.424
Comes faster every year.

06:50.703 --> 06:51.866
It does.

06:57.225 --> 06:58.549
They're not here, Frankie.

07:04.377 --> 07:06.207
I'm so confused.

07:06.526 --> 07:08.394
I mean,
Brad is an amazing friend

07:08.498 --> 07:11.314
and he has always been there
for me, and he'll do my makeup.

07:11.450 --> 07:13.883
But Sean drove all the way down
from Notre Dame

07:13.988 --> 07:15.457
just to take me.

07:15.596 --> 07:16.974
What do you think I should do?

07:19.229 --> 07:21.237
Oh. Ha ha.
Very funny, Axl.

07:21.344 --> 07:23.438
You know, this is
a very serious issue

07:23.517 --> 07:25.040
and a lot of people's feelings
are at stake

07:25.110 --> 07:26.894
and you are not being
very supportive!

07:27.484 --> 07:28.239
Aah!

07:31.113 --> 07:32.696
You. Me. Prom.

07:32.781 --> 07:34.780
Pick me up at 7:00.
Show some leg.

07:34.861 --> 07:36.331
Are you -- What --

07:36.427 --> 07:37.583
No, no, no, but I-I--

07:38.631 --> 07:39.771
Ha.

07:42.247 --> 07:43.657
Yeah. Right.

07:51.541 --> 07:52.632
You know what?

07:52.719 --> 07:53.540
Maybe we've just said

07:53.631 --> 07:55.239
everything we've had to say
to each other.

07:55.324 --> 07:57.344
You wanted to bring it,
I wanted to bring it.

07:57.479 --> 07:59.420
Maybe there's
just nothing to bring.

07:59.719 --> 08:01.292
This is why we should never
leave the couch.

08:01.384 --> 08:02.729
Let the cable company bring it.

08:02.831 --> 08:03.937
Yeah, that's fine for now.

08:04.064 --> 08:06.265
But when the kids leave,
it's just gonna be you and me,

08:06.361 --> 08:07.642
and we're not gonna have
anything to talk about.

08:07.737 --> 08:10.365
Then we're just gonna be two old
people staring at each other.

08:10.444 --> 08:11.386
We won't be alone.

08:11.473 --> 08:13.337
Brick will be here,
jumbling up our meds.

08:13.419 --> 08:15.128
I'm just saying,
if we want to have any prayer

08:15.219 --> 08:15.967
of an interesting life,

08:16.065 --> 08:18.385
we're gonna have to bring
other people into it.

08:18.652 --> 08:20.123
You know what we should do?

08:20.202 --> 08:21.428
I know it's not
your favorite thing,

08:21.516 --> 08:22.880
but I think we should have
a dinner party.

08:22.957 --> 08:24.462
You know, we used to have

08:24.550 --> 08:26.220
those Memorial Day barbecues
every year.

08:26.304 --> 08:28.767
We put the keg on the porch.
Remember?

08:28.898 --> 08:31.032
I mean, we used to be fun,
social people, Mike.

08:31.106 --> 08:32.703
I've seen the pictures.

08:32.881 --> 08:33.732
Hmm.

08:34.115 --> 08:35.508
I am pretty bored
of talking to you.

08:35.587 --> 08:38.548
Exactly, and I'm totally sick
of talking to you.

08:39.509 --> 08:41.306
Sure. What the hell?

08:41.399 --> 08:42.381
Let's do it.

08:44.679 --> 08:45.722
I love books.

08:45.850 --> 08:47.206
Do you remember
"Pat The Bunny"?

08:47.379 --> 08:48.654
You could feel the bunny.

08:49.066 --> 08:49.830
Oh.

08:50.181 --> 08:51.398
Hey, Darrin.

08:51.642 --> 08:52.624
Hey, Sue.

08:52.712 --> 08:54.404
- No-no-no-no-no! Bup-bup-bup!
- No, wait!

08:54.869 --> 08:55.756
No!!

08:56.005 --> 08:57.018
Oops.

08:57.698 --> 08:58.703
Sorry.

